## Version Compliance

- Target: [YOUR_FRAMEWORK] [VERSION]
- [Framework-specific version rules, e.g., deprecated APIs to avoid]
- [Required patterns for this version]

## Language Rules

| Context | Language | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| User-facing content | [YOUR_UI_LANGUAGE] | [Conventions, e.g., inclusive language] |
| Code, comments, XML IDs | English | Always |
| Commit messages, docs | English | Always |

## Security

- Every new model requires access control configuration
- Row-level security for portal/public access
- `copy=False` (or equivalent) on tokens, UUIDs, credentials
- Input validation on all external-facing endpoints

## Quality

- ALWAYS verify work after implementation -- testing is critical
- ONE feature per session; use `/clear` when starting a new feature
- Start complex tasks in Plan mode (Shift+Tab)
- Use framework ORM -- never raw SQL unless absolutely necessary

## .context System

Read these files before writing code:

1. `.context/substrate.md` -- Navigation hub
2. `.context/ai-rules.md` -- Hard coding constraints
3. `.context/glossary.md` -- Domain terminology

## Workflow

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `/flow-resume` | Start session, restore context |
| `/flow-start <#>` | Pick up issue, create branch |
| `/flow-ship` | Commit, push, create PR |
| `/flow-handover` | End session, save state |
| `/flow-status` | Show current work state |
| `/flow-reflect` | Synthesize learnings |

